//
// Regression fixture: R5 (operator spacing) MUST fire on a
// `TransferStmt` rhs nested inside a `proc` body — the
// `formatNode(ProcDefn)` recursion override delegates to the
// body Stmt (typically a `ParallelBlock` or `SeqBlock`), which
// then routes the formatter into each item, and finally into
// the inner `TransferStmt`. Same pattern as the func-body
// fixture in `transfer-rhs.test`; this one pins the proc-body
// path explicitly.

// RUN: echo 'module m { reg q[8]; proc_name pn(q); proc pn { q:=a+b; } }' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: q := a + b;
